        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 1:22AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 122 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
south of Red Rock, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Ralston...                        Pawnee...
Sooner Lake...                    Fairfax...
Kaw Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
